The sixty-piece Pretoria Symphony Orchestra under the leadership of Schalk J. van der Merwe will perform well-known classical masterpieces on the banks of the Hennops River.Tickets cost R200 per person and include a complimentary wine tasting. Guests will be able to enjoy a culinary journey at one of the two award-winning restaurants from 12:00 on the day.Come and experience the exquisite combination of good food, award winning wines and classical music in a relaxed outside setting. Date: Sunday, 4 June 2017 Time: 14:30 16:30 Price: Adults: R200 (includes free wine tasting)Duration: Two hours (including a 30 minute interval)Tickets are available at Computicket: http://online.computicket.com/web/event/symphony&nbsp;